After wandering a ways, and some savings of the Sword Coast, Minsc returned to Rashemen. To find a welcome fit for hamsters and heroes!
Indeed! A berserker after my own heart. Though hers is made of hellish heat, and metal, and... some manner of coin-operated device?
Who is Halsin?
But if Minsc can become calm, perhaps evil will learn to fear his serenity.
You'll like him - he reminds me of you a little.
That is why Minsc always speaks his mind. LOUDLY.
Talk about something else.
Boo speaks of much - perhaps, one day, you will be ready to listen.
...I know you mean well, my friend. But Boo, being your friend, wishes to share some of this cold and pointy truth I mention.
There is power in the wychlaran bond. Far too much to be wasted on weeping. To use that power to serve the living does not sully the dead - it honours them.
And Minthara is - eh. A friend of yours, I am sure.
I tell you, he grew pale as death itself. He licked his lips, and trembled so violently that Minsc thought he might faint on the spot!
But it is like the city too. Here, it is loud with the daily wailing of people. In Rashemen, it is also loud - if you know where to listen.
As you wish. Boo? Do you have much to say on the matter of 'something else'?
Evil is my enemy - and I have two boots. One can stomp righteously on Sharran skulls while the other kicks the Absolute about the place.
This is why Boo favours the spot just above my buttocks.
Correct! There are more whiskers on Boo's tiny face than on the mighty chin of Minsc!

EditorData.NodeContext: Boo squeaks before Minsc's line

Text.Value: So be like Boo, and fight with the weapons nature gave you.
You're a true warrior, Minsc - you don't need a petty thing like weapons.
It was only polite for Minsc to agree.
Aw. Do you see? This is the manner of compliment that only good friends pay to one another!
You travelled a hundred years in a moment - what do you make of this new world?
A fabulous tattoo.
What is your fondest memory of adventuring with Bhaalspawn?
Eh, Boo has said it is unkind to speak behind the backs of some of our companions.
Well. In many ways, it is the very opposite of this city. The far side of Faern, with empty plains, white forests, and peaks that pierce the very belly of the sky!
To each wychlaran is bonded a berserker bodyguard. To dog her heels and watch her back, until death claims one or both.
Jaheira says Minsc and Boo were often draped in flowers, and showered with wine. Still as stone, but the life of the party nonetheless!
Boo is here. My steel is here. Jaheira's face has more lines, but her tongue and wits are as sharp as ever.
Maybe someday you'll trust me enough to tell the real tale.
Minsc says that you are perhaps not as righteous or sweet-smelling as you believe.
I just need to know you're going to listen to her from now on. To me.
If my meaning is not clear... just check under your boot.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referencing the probable shit on our shoes.

Text.Value: I don't think all of the Sharrans were evil - some were just misguided.
You can admit it. You're not a little bit jealous of his legend?
Soft-spoken. Hates curses. Loves trees.
Somehow such a person as you describe has entirely escaped Minsc's notice. How strange.
Ahh, you come in search of stories? It is not yet time to tuck Boo in for the night - but very well!
You're both giant, hulking do-gooders. I thought you'd get along.
If such a tiny puny druid-man reminds you of Minsc, I think the tadpole may have made a feast of your brain!
Boo and I, we thank you for your kind words, my friend. But Minsc knows when he has made a mess that is for him, and him alone to clean.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, warm, appreciates us trying

Text.Value: Your gaze is naturally caught on my handsome face - the face that is loved by all - but cast your eyes down. Just a little. Not so far as to make Minsc blush.
The Boot of Backsides, perhaps? Or -
The telthors: guardian spirits of every root, rock, and tree. Here in the Sleeping Lands they are silent - but in the far north, they know how to speak still.
My people know of your berserkers, too. They make for fine and challenging prey.
Leave.
I think I understand your meaning. Then Jaheira is my wychlaran - and so are you. You are my wychlaran!
How did you come to trust the spawn of such an evil god?
That's what I said.
Hah - well, may he answer to the archdevil herself, and may all her questions be hot pokers pressed against his flesh!
The githyanki may have Minsc of Rashemen's ire; sometimes, healthy servings of his sword; but for this, and this alone, they shall always have his respect.
Let's talk about something else.
Enough joking. Does the hamster actually speak to you?
Can you not? Do you not see his noble bearing? The deep wells of wisdom that are his eyes?
You suggest that Minsc uses the term lightly? Simply leaps from Dynaheir to Jaheira, with no caring for the custom itself? An unworthy thought - and WRONG!
And Gale is my wychlaran!
You chased after me, time and again, and saved me when you did not even know me - we are already 'more than friends'.
I had hoped we had grown a little closer than that.
You travelled with Bhaalspawn before, didn't you? What do you know of them?
It's simple - the end justifies the means.
Minsc is an open book, with many pretty pictures.
The first time - my dajemma. A warrior's quest of proving. Minsc quickly proved that quests do not always go as the stories say.
It sounds like an amazing place. Why did you ever leave?
Of the drow I can say only this - she may be treacherous, vicious, and much meaner than she has any need to be. But she is clearly no cleverer than Minsc.
Just last night, Minsc was dressing one of his many heroic wounds in camp - when Astarion stumbled upon the scene.
You do not know this custom? Great Rashemen is ruled by the Masked Ones - wise women you might call 'witches'.
Not minding is one of the many things Minsc is known for!
You are of the same blood as our old friend: a Bhaalspawn, and as close to Minsc as if they were his own kin.
You inspired people even as a statue.
There is a lesson in this. We are born into a bloodline, yes - but we need not be bound by it.
I'd like to know your thoughts on our companions.
Oh, the tiny puny elf with leaves in his hair, and dirt under his fingernails.
Boo speaks sense, as ever. There is goodness in Wyll - we have seen it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Boo squeaks up in Wyll's defence before Minsc's line.

Text.Value: Hm. So... duty, camaraderie, help in troubled times - what I call the bond of a wychlaran, you simply call... friendship?
Gortash sold her to Zariel. He had a lot to answer for.
The problem with one so gazing of their navel, however - they are easily ambushed. Brigands split my skull like a sodden wine-skin.
When Sarevok's butt had been kicked so hard that we thought he would never return, we settled in Baldur's Gate for a while.
That's nothing to do with being a wychlaran - it's just called being a friend.
The mind of Minsc was occupied with important matters. I was browsing at a slum vendor's stall, looking for Boo's favourite nuts.
That is what I remember, more than any battles against Bhaal and his spawn.

EditorData.NodeContext: fondly reminiscing - lower volume than usual

Text.Value: I'll let him tell you himself.
Let's talk about something else.
Did he take a bath in the River Styx and temporarily forget himself? I do not remember.
You should give him a break - he's only trying to help.
Hah, you think we are the prey? Our warriors only stopped hoarding your hides because they made for such poor leather.
Speak of something else.
All you told me about the old days: you seem so positive for someone who's lost so much.
You clearly care for one another - so enough of the arguing.
GALE! MY GOOD FRIEND! WHERE ARE YOU? MINSC AND BOO WOULD LIKE TO HEAR ABOUT THE EXPLODING.
But Minsc, of course, will translate.
This is so in Rashemen - but not beyond her borders. Here, the spirits sleep - and perhaps we ought to be glad of this.
Thank you. It's nice not having to justify myself for once.
Aha! Perhaps this is the reason, Boo. It is not because of the legendary thickness of my skull.
What was it like being a statue?
But there is no glory without action, and no valour without violence!
I... do not think so? Minsc has always been Minsc, except for the times he was stone or Stone Lord.
Did he travel with a spawn of the god of murder, who warred against his evil brethren, and battled triumphantly at the Throne of Bhaal itself?
And I am in total agreement. See? No arguing.
I think you're just describing a friend.
I hope you're right.
You've told me about Rashemen - but why did you leave?
Rashemen sounds like an interesting place. Why did you leave?
So it was with Minsc and his witch, Dynaheir. Until she died, and Minsc had to carry on without her.
He's not puny - he's huge!
Lae'zel is not her people. Nor am I.
I'd like to hear your take on someone else.
Not long after, Minsc and Boo were captured, and Dynaheir was dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: fondly reminiscing - lower volume than usual

Text.Value: As long as that stench remains, no matter how old or young the world is, Minsc and Boo will not rest.
We shall not know which side has won until it hits the earth, I think. So cough it up, Boo!

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug - serene about her struggle as it is her choice. But a little bit annoyed about the coin

Text.Value: It's sweet that you and Jaheira still have one another after all this time.
Closer? Hah! You could only be closer if you were to wriggle beneath my blankets with Boo!
After they carried the Iron Lord away, the council of witches gave Minsc a pack of provisions, and said it would be best if he continued his adventures for a time.
You clearly care for one another - so enough of the arguing.
Sorcerous Sundries. Dynaheir fell in love. Dragged poor Minsc there every day, and made him stand watch while she browsed the shelves.

EditorData.NodeContext: fondly reminiscing - lower volume than usual

Text.Value: You have power - and you decided how to use it. No one else.
You don't have a beard.
Jaheira did her part, of course, but she prefers to scowl from the shadows. The city needs a name - a face! Preferably, a furry companion too.
They do not sing of the times in between.

Synopsis: Minsc's default dialogue. In the current entries, he reflects on his opinion of us and our adventures so far, as well as revealing a little of history.
